gomodel:SYNGO_2008  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.6 \"β3-containing nAChRs mediate striatal dopamine release\"\nThe application of nicotine to striatal synaptosomes stimulates the release of dopamine. This response can be inhibited by nicotinic antogonist α-conotoxin MII. Sensitivity to α-conotoxin MII is reduced in preparations of a beta3 KO mouse.. Experimental description: \"The perfusion method used to examine the release of [3H]dopamine from mouse striatal synaptosomes has been described previously (Grady et al., 2002)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2008" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .
